(firstQuint)Polarstem Cementless Hip Stem.

 The goal of this multicenter clinical observation is to validate short-, mid-, and long-term outcome (efficacy and safety) of the POLARSTEM cent .

 Efficacy evaluations: - Evaluation of function, range of motion (ROM) and pain as assessed by Harris Hip Score, Hip disability and osteoarthritis outcome score (HOOS) [7, 8], an extension of the Western Ontario and McMaster Universities Osteoarthritis Index (WOMAC).

 - Radiographic changes as defined by radiolucent lines, osteolysis, hypo- and hypertrophy, implant loosening or migration Safety evaluations: - Intra- and perioperative device-related adverse events (AE) and complications up to discharge - Postoperative AE up to 10 years.

